<P>
Mexican Art Exhibit to Open: The first comprehensive exhibit of Mexican art to 
be shown in the United States since before World War II will open at the 
Metropolitan Museum of Art in New York on Oct. 10 and travel later to San 
Antonio, Tex., and Los Angeles, it was announced Monday. Philippe de 
Montebello, director of the Met, said more than 400 works from public and 
private collections in Mexico, Europe and the United States will be displayed 
at the museum through Jan. 13, 1991. The show will trace 30 centuries of visual 
arts in Mexico, from 1000 BC to 1950. GREG BRAXTON 
