<TEXT>
<P>
Neil Sedaka to Undergo Surgery: Singer-songwriter Neil Sedaka, hospitalized 
since last week with an intestinal ailment, has decided to have surgery to 
correct the problem, said hospital officials in Danbury, Conn. 
</P>
<P>
Sedaka, 51, will probably undergo surgery in the next week. Sedaka, who lives 
in Westport, Conn., was admitted to Danbury Hospital last Tuesday suffering 
from diverticulitis, an inflammation of the colon. The singer, who was listed 
in good and stable condition Monday, planned to remain in the hospital until 
the surgery is performed. It was not immediately known how long the surgery 
would take or what the recuperation period would be. GREG BRAXTON 
