<P>
RANCHO MIRAGE; 
</P>
<P>
GIRL KILLED IN DRAG-RACING CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times staff and Wire reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A teen-age girl on spring break was killed in a head-on collision with a car 
drag-racing on a highway near Palm Springs, authorities said. Another young 
woman and two youths were also hurt in the collision on California 111 in 
Rancho Mirage, about 10 miles southeast of the desert spa city, where tens of 
thousands of students have converged for an annual weeklong party that begins 
with springtime vacation at high schools and colleges. 
</P>
<P>
Timare Blanke, 17, of Corona, died at a hospital shortly after the crash, 
Riverside County sheriff's deputies said. A passenger in Blanke's car, Chin 
Huang, 18, of Anaheim, was treated at the same hospital for minor injuries. The 
names and condition of two 16-year-old Torrance boys in the other car were not 
released. The wreckage and victims "were scattered for about three blocks," 
Police Lt. Lee Weigel said. 
</P>
