<P>
MOTORCYCLIST MAGEE CRITICAL AFTER CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SAN JOSE 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Australian motorcycle racer Kevin Magee was listed in critical condition Monday 
after surgery to remove a blood clot on his brain sustained in an accident at 
the U.S. Grand Prix, a hospital spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
Magee crashed his 500cc Suzuki Sunday on the second lap of the 35-lap feature 
race at Laguna Seca Raceway. The race was restarted after Magee was airlifted 
to San Jose Medical Center for treatment. 
</P>
<P>
Christi Welter, public relations director of the hospital, said Monday that 
Magee had undergone a CAT scan earlier in the day. The results were not 
immediately available. 
