<HEADLINE>
<P>
LORENZONI UPSETS ETERNAL FLIGHT FOR RECORD PICK SIX AT AQUEDUCT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Lorenzoni held off favored Eternal Flight in the stretch Monday to win the 
$31,000 Mr. Prospector Purse by 1 1/4 lengths at Aqueduct. 
</P>
<P>
Laurent Goossens rode Lorenzoni to his first victory in four starts this year 
and only the third in 14 career starts. 
</P>
<P>
One of those victories was over Easy Goer in a six-furlong sprint on Aug. 1, 
1988. 
</P>
<P>
Eternal Flight, with Chris Antley aboard, was second in the field of six 
3-year-olds and older, 1 3/4 lengths ahead of Clef. 
</P>
<P>
Lorenzoni covered seven furlongs in 1:22 2/5 on the fast track to earn $18,600 
and returned $15.40, $4.40 and $3.40. Eternal Flight paid $2.60 and $2.60 and 
Clef was $4.20. 
</P>
<P>
Lorenzoni's victory capped a record high Pick Six payoff of $767,998 for one 
Aqueduct patron. The largest previous pick six payoff in New York was the 
$666,735 paid to a single on-track patron on Oct. 26,1989. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Game Story; Wire 
</P>
</TYPE>
