<TEXT>
<P>
Com Systems, a Van Nuys-based long-distance telecommunications operator, said 
it sold 4.5 million shares of its Series C cumulative convertible preferred 
stock for $9 million, and $13 million of its five-year, 11.5% convertible 
subordinated debentures to OmniCorp International B.V. 
</P>
<P>
The preferred stock is convertible into 4.5 million shares of Com Systems 
common stock, and the debentures are convertible into 2.9 million shares of 
common stock. 
</P>
