<TEXT>
<P>
CANCERWATCH: News that the state is unveiling a tough anti-smoking campaign 
(A3) got a warm reception in Orange County. "It's tremendous!" exulted local 
American Cancer Society spokesman Kirk Wilks. Already, he noted, fewer people 
are believed to be smoking here (20%, down from 50% three decades ago). . . . 
Even so, lung cancer deaths here are up from 645 in 1979 to at least 878 last 
year. Lanie Jones and Eric Bailey 
</P>
