<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Kenneth Williams 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Sculptors are invited to submit slides of their work for possible placement in 
the city of Brea's consignment art program, which installs pieces for one-year 
periods on publicly owned property. One location awaiting art is a newly 
landscaped area at the intersection of Lambert Road and the Orange Freeway. 
</P>
<P>
Work will be selected by the city's Cultural Arts Commission, which makes 
recommendations to the City Council. The city will pay for transportation and 
installation costs, as well as insurance. The rationale for the project is that 
developers required to purchase works of art in accordance with the city's Art 
in Public Places program would be exposed on a regular basis to a range of 
potential selections. For more information, call Scott Riordan, program 
coordinator in the Brea Community Services Department: (714) 990-7723. 
</P>
