</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Wire Services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
LYSEKIL, Sweden 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rescuers said that the total number of people burned to death and drowned in 
the Scandinavian Star ferry fire disaster may never be known, and police 
expressed confidence today that they will find the arsonist believed to be 
responsible. 
</P>
<P>
The ferry, sailing from Oslo to Denmark, caught fire early Saturday south of 
the Oslo Fjord with about 500 passengers and crew aboard. Police in Oslo 
confirmed that 176 people had died but suggested that the toll may eventually 
top 200. 
</P>
<P>
In Copenhagen, officials were preparing for Wednesday's opening of a board of 
inquiry to explain Saturday's disaster, working on the "concrete theory that it 
was arson." 
