<HEADLINE>
<P>
READER'S DIGEST TO PUBLISH FRENCH 'BUDGETS FAMILLE' 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
NEW YORK 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Reader's Digest Assn. Inc. said today it will launch a new monthly magazine in 
France this fall as part of the publishing company's strategy to expand 
operations overseas. 
</P>
<P>
Budgets Famille (Family Budgets) will contain news, feature articles and tips 
on topics ranging from savings and borrowing strategies to the best ways 
families can budget for their children's education as well as leisure 
activities like vacation," said Reader's Digest, the publisher of the most 
widely read magazine in the world. 
</P>
<P>
Budgets Famille, to debut on French newsstands in October, will target the 30- 
to 45-year-old parents in upper- and middle-income families, the publisher 
said. 
</P>
<P>
Budgets Famille is Reader's Digest's first foreign start-up publication since 
the company announced last year a plan to expand its operations overseas 
through acquisitions and the launching of new special interest magazines. 
</P>
<P>
"It is too early to disclose sales or advertisements projections for Budgets 
Famille at this stage," said spokesman Bruce Trachtenberg. "But we are 
confident the publication will meet the demand." 
</P>
<P>
Henri Capdeville, managing director for the publishing group's French division, 
noted that while there are a number of French business magazines focusing on 
personal finances, none cover specific family issues. The French edition of 
Reader's Digest, called Selection, has a monthly circulation of 1.1 million. 
</P>
<P>
"We think Budgets Famille will provide an ideal target market for advertisers," 
Capdeville said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
